3. 養聲

廣東話：你把聲沙晒，呢幾日都係講少啲嘢養下聲啦。
English: Your voice is completely hoarse; you should talk less and rest your voice for the next few days.

4. 票尾

廣東話：記住留返張票尾，遲啲攞去報銷呀。
English: Remember to keep the ticket stub for reimbursement later.

5. hacker

廣東話：聽講嗰間公司嘅系統俾hacker入侵咗，搞到好多客戶資料外洩。
English: I heard that company's system was hacked, causing a lot of customer data to leak.

6. 石斛蘭

廣東話：石斛蘭同一般種喺泥入面嘅蘭花唔同，佢哋係會依附喺樹上面生長嘅。
English: Dendrobium orchids are different from ordinary orchids planted in soil; they grow attached to trees.

7. 吊詭 (矛盾、悖論)

廣東話：呢個故事嘅結局真係好吊詭，完全同之前嘅鋪排自相矛盾。
English: The ending of this story is truly paradoxical; it completely contradicts the previous setup.

8. 吊詭 (似非而是、荒謬)

廣東話：佢明明做錯事，反而仲可以升職，呢個世界真係好吊詭。
English: He clearly did something wrong, yet he still got promoted; this world is truly absurd.

9. 各為其主

廣東話：我哋以前雖然係好兄弟，但係而家大家各為其主，對陣嘅時候絕唔會手軟。
English: Although we used to be good brothers, now we each serve our own masters, and we definitely won't show mercy when facing each other.

10. 軨蓋

廣東話：架車隻軨蓋俾人刮花咗，要去車房噴過油。
English: The hubcap of the car got scratched, so I need to go to the garage to get it repainted.

11. 打哥夫

廣東話：放假嘅時候，我鍾意同班朋友去打哥夫，當做運動吓。
English: During holidays, I like to go play golf with my friends as a form of exercise.

12. 免揀

廣東話：呢批特價生果係免揀嘅，唔好自己揀揀擇擇呀。
English: This batch of discounted fruits is non-selectable; don't pick and choose.

13. 擺闊佬

廣東話：佢次次出街食飯都搶住畀錢，真係鍾意擺闊佬。
English: Every time we eat out, he rushes to pay the bill; he really likes to show off his wealth.

14. 廣播劇

廣東話：以前好多人收工返到屋企，最鍾意就係扭開收音機聽廣播劇。
English: In the past, many people's favorite thing to do after getting home from work was to turn on the radio and listen to radio dramas.

15. 錄影機

廣東話：以前要錄低電視節目，就一定要用錄影機同錄影帶。
English: In the past, to record TV programs, you had to use a video recorder and videotapes.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩

廣東話：而家證據確鑿，你吟詩吟唔甩㗎啦，快啲認罪啦！
English: The evidence is irrefutable now; you can't talk your way out of it, so confess quickly!

17. 佈道大會

廣東話：教會今個禮拜日會喺大球場搞個大型嘅佈道大會。
English: The church will hold a large-scale evangelistic rally at the stadium this Sunday.

18. 寫手 (寫作的人)

廣東話：佢係一個全職寫手，每日都會寫幾千字嘅小說。
English: He is a full-time writer who writes several thousand words of novels every day.

19. 寫手 (代替他人寫作的人)

廣東話：個議員俾人踢爆啲文章全靠請寫手代筆，根本唔係自己寫嘅。
English: The politician was exposed for relying entirely on ghostwriters for his articles; he didn't write them himself at all.

20. 代打

廣東話：我今晚要加班，你可唔可以幫我代打，做下每日任務呀？
English: I have to work overtime tonight; can you help me play and do the daily quests?

21. 茶碗

廣東話：呢隻日本茶碗好精緻，一定好貴啦。
English: This Japanese tea bowl is very exquisite; it must be very expensive.

22. 茶隔

廣東話：斟茶嗰陣記得用個茶隔隔走啲茶葉，唔係嘅話會飲到成口渣。
English: Remember to use a tea strainer to filter out the tea leaves when pouring tea, otherwise you'll end up with a mouthful of dregs.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈

廣東話：老闆自己遲到就冇事，我哋遲到一分鐘就扣人工，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈！
English: The boss is fine when he's late, but if we are one minute late our salary gets docked; it's truly "only the officials are allowed to set fires, while the common people are forbidden to light lamps"!

24. 獨唱

廣東話：今晚個晚會，佢會負責獨唱嗰首主題曲。
English: At tonight's gala, she will be responsible for the solo of the theme song.

25. 快人快事

廣東話：李生做嘢最爽快，真係快人快事，頭先傾完而家已經簽好合約。
English: Mr. Li works most efficiently; he is truly a swift person doing swift things. We just finished talking and the contract is already signed.

26. 四腳獸

廣東話：聽講商場個公廁又俾人撞破有四腳獸，真係離譜！
English: I heard that someone was caught being a "four-legged beast" in the mall's public restroom again; it's really outrageous!

27. 無米粥

廣東話：嗰單生意而家仲係煲無米粥嘅階段，細節咩都未傾好，唔好咁快話實呀。
English: That business deal is still at the "cooking riceless porridge" stage; none of the details have been negotiated, so don't say it's a done deal so quickly.

28. 義會

廣東話：以前基層市民好難向銀行借錢，有需要嗰陣好多時都係靠朋友之間搞義會嚟周轉。
English: In the past, it was very difficult for grassroots citizens to borrow money from banks; when in need, they often relied on organizing rotating savings and credit associations among friends for cash flow.

29. 榜文

廣東話：縣衙門出面貼咗張榜文，重金懸賞緝拿嗰個江洋大盜。
English: A notice was posted outside the county magistrate's office, offering a heavy reward for the capture of that notorious robber.

30. MK名

廣東話：而家仲有人用「堅系·愛你」呢啲MK名做網名咩？真係好騎呢！
English: Are there still people using "MK names" like "Absolutely·LoveYou" as online names nowadays? It's really weird! [end of text]


